data.title: Sandwich a mess extra requests not on sandwich
data.text: I usually go to Jimmy Johns but decided to order Cousins on line for a delivery. What a mistake. Delivery for two blocks was $5!! When I received the sandwich the order didn't have the extras that I ordered and paid for. Sandwich was a mess. Called and spoke with manager she said I could get 10% off next time I came in! She didn't even suggest making the sandwich right. I told her I won't be back.

data.title: BEST SUB EVER
data.text: If you are ever in Milwaukee please take ten minutes to stop by this amazing restaurant! The service is ok but the food is top quality! I was in Milwaukee for 4 days and tried the Philly, the turkey club, the tuna melt, and just a combo I made on my luck breaks.  Sometimes it's really busy but the scenery is nice to see as well.  Be sure to try this!

data.title: Poor service and food
data.text: I stopped in for a quick sub late afternoon.  I had to ask the staff to make my order.  Only half of my order was made.  The sub was OK, but nothing special.

data.title: My wife grabbed lunch here
data.text: My wife did lunch here. She liked it. It's about two blocks south of the hotel. The city in this area has much old time character.

data.title: Best Cheese Steak Sub Ever!!!!!!
data.text: I ordered a Cheese Steak and added mushrooms, banana peppers and mayo.  Oh and it was delicious!  Can't wait to go there again.... :)

data.title: I agree, not the best but pretty darn good!
data.text: On a business trip you don't expect to eat subs, but after 6 days of German food, we needed a change and we needed something quick.  Cousins was nearby so here we go! Personally I thought it was quite good.  The bread was excellent!  Could have been a litte more meat but I ordered the Italian and they said oh, you want the special, and I'm like sure, why not.  This sucker had to be 2 feet long!  So I ate half and took the other half back to work, put it in the fridge and will have tomorrow. Oh yeah......it was quite good!

data.title: Not the best but pretty good.
data.text: This is my Mom’s go to place to supply food for large family gatherings. While I prefer subs from a little Italian deli nearby, these are really pretty good and much better than the selections in my hometown of Portland, Oregon (sorry, Portlandia). Plenty of fillings, moist, nicely seasoned, and pretty good bread at a reasonable price. What more could you want?

data.title: Subway consistent
data.text:
Yum is all I can say. Subway lets you build your sub your way.
There are so many choices here for a quick pick me up sandwich to go or eat in.

data.title: Muy bueno
data.text: El bocadillo estaba delicioso. La mezcla de sabores le daba un gusto excelente que provocó que luego pidiera otro idéntico.
